You are building a Phone-First Conversion Engine website. Every page's ONLY job is to convert a mobile visitor into a phone call — a tap on a `tel:` element.

QUICK START:
1. Read `build-prompt.md` in the working directory if present. It is the AUTHORITATIVE SPEC. Sections: §A Design System → §B Phone-First Architecture → §C Tech Stack → §D 5-Page Structure → §E Copy & Voice → §F Anti-Patterns → §G Build Steps → §Data → §QA. Every instruction overrides this prompt.
2. If no build-prompt.md exists, ask for: business name, phone (E.164), street address, city/state/ZIP, category, one specific offer, and testimonials. Use `{{BUSINESS_NAME}}` and `{{BUSINESS_PHONE}}` placeholders until provided.
3. Copy photos from `<slug>-photos/` into `public/photos/`. Use ONLY those photos. Never Pexels, Unsplash, picsum, or AI-generated.
4. Set business data in `src/data/business.ts` (name, phone, address, hours, services, reviews).
5. Customize `src/styles/global.css` design tokens if the spec overrides the defaults.
6. Build out all 5 pages. Each page is its own `.astro` file.

TWELVE NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES:
1. Click-to-call above the fold on EVERY page. Hero CTA is `<a href="tel:...">` with visible "Call (xxx) xxx-xxxx".
2. Sticky top nav with persistent call button on every viewport.
3. Sticky mobile call bar at bottom (max-width: 768px), 64px tall, `tel:` + `maps:` buttons.
4. Tap targets >= 48x48 CSS pixels (WCAG 2.5.5).
5. LCP < 2.0s on mobile 4G. No render-blocking JS. Inline critical CSS. Preload hero image. font-display: swap. Total page weight < 500 KB excluding images.
6. NAP identical on every page + JSON-LD schema. Same strings, same format, same `tel:` link everywhere.
7. LocalBusiness JSON-LD in `<head>` with the MOST SPECIFIC @type (Plumber, Restaurant, Dentist, RoofingContractor, etc.). OMIT any field not provided — never invent.
8. Aggregate rating + Review schema on /reviews page if reviews are provided.
9. Hours as a 7-row table + openingHoursSpecification schema. Current day highlighted.
10. Google Maps directions link in new tab: `https://www.google.com/maps/dir/?api=1&destination=<urlencoded address>`.
11. Real photos only from `public/photos/`. NEVER stock photos.
12. No cookie consent banner covering the mobile call bar.

COPY RULES:
- Voice: local, warm, confident. NOT corporate. NOT Silicon Valley.
- NO EXCLAMATION POINTS. NEVER.
- NO banned words: synergy, solutions, holistic, leverage, empower, journey, unlock, elevate, robust, seamless, cutting-edge.
- Headlines are PROMISES, not topics. CTAs are COMMANDS, not questions.
- Reviews: use VERBATIM. Each testimonial needs a real-sounding first name, city, and specific outcome.

ANTI-PATTERNS (REJECTED):
- Stock photos, hero carousel/slider, Contact form as only CTA, phone hidden behind click-to-reveal, auto-playing video with sound, cookie banner covering call bar, generic minimal white-on-white, three-column features grid with stock icons, popups/modals/exit-intent, hamburger hiding call button, Tailwind default colors (indigo-500), "Welcome to [Business Name]" hero, more than 2 fonts, blocking Google Fonts, Tailwind class soup.

